title: Encyclopedia of Concert Music (Art Ebook)
description:
Hill and Wang | 1959 | Pdf | Eng | 566 pag | 79.5 MB

This superb volume provides the answers to all basic questions about instrumental and concert music. It will increase the reader's knowledge and enrich the listening experience of every music-loving family. There are thousands of entries alphabetically arranged and cross-indexed for easy reference. Among the subjects covered are: Musical Compositions, Composers, Performers and Performances, Musical Terms, Musical Instruments, History and Background of Music, Theories and Theorists of Music, Literary and Artistic Sources, and many special articles.
Based on years of research and a lifetime devoted to musical scholarship, the Encyclopedia of Concert Music is essential to any home library
